1.q_string: Which one of the following is the balanced redox reaction of \(\mathrm{AsO}_{3}^{3-}+\) \(\mathrm{MnO}_{4}^{-} \longrightarrow \mathrm{AsO}_{4}^{-}+\mathrm{MnO}_{2}\) (in alkaline medium)?

An evacuated glass vessel weighs \(50 \mathrm{~g}\) when empty, \(148 \mathrm{~g}\) when filled with a liquid of density \(0.98 \mathrm{~g} / \mathrm{ml}\) and \(50.5 \mathrm{~g}\) when filled with an ideal gas at \(760 \mathrm{~mm} \mathrm{Hg}\) at \(300 \mathrm{~K}\). The molecular weight of the gas is:

\(7.35 \mathrm{~g}\) of a dibasic acid was dissolved is water and diluted to \(250 \mathrm{ml}\). \(25 \mathrm{ml}\) of this solution was neutralised by \(15 \mathrm{ml}\) of \(\mathrm{N}\) \(\mathrm{NaOH}\) solution. The molecular weight of the acid will be:
Which of the following statements indicates that law of multiple proportion is being followed?
q_option: Carbon forms two oxides namely \(\mathrm{CO}_{2}\) and \(\mathrm{CO}\), where masses of oxygen which combine with fixed mass of carbon are in the simple ratio \(2: 1\).
When magnesium burns in oxygen, the amount of magnesium taken for the reaction is equal to the amount of magnesium in magnesium oxide formed.
Sample of carbon dioxide taken from any source will always have carbon and oxygen in the ratio \(1:2\).
At constant temperature and pressure \(200 \mathrm{~mL}\) of hydrogen will combine with \(100 \mathrm{~mL}\) oxygen to produce \(200 \mathrm{~mL}\) of water vapour.

1.q_string: One mole of any substance contains \(6.022 \times 10^{23}\) atoms/molecules. Number of molecules of \(\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}\) present in \(100 \mathrm{~mL}\) of \(0.02 \mathrm{M} \mathrm{~H}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}\) solution is:

A solution of glucose \(\left(\mathrm{C}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{12} \mathrm{O}_{6}\right)\) in water is labelled as \(10 \%\) by weight. What would be the molality of the solution?

\(\left(\right.\) Molar mass of glucose \(=180 \mathrm{~g} \mathrm{~mol}^{-1}\) )
Which one of the following statements about a compound is incorrect?
q_option: A molecule of a compound has atoms of different elements.
A compound cannot be separated into its constituent elements by physical methods of separation.
A compound retains the physical properties of its constituent elements.
The ratio of atoms of different elements in a compound is fixed.

1.q_string:
Which of the following statements is correct about the reaction given below?

\(4 \mathrm{Fe}(\mathrm{s})+3 \mathrm{O}_{2}(\mathrm{~g}) \rightarrow 2 \mathrm{Fe}_{2} \mathrm{O}_{3}(\mathrm{~g})\)
q_option: The total mass of reactants \(=\) Total mass of the products. It follows the law of conservation of mass.
The total mass of reactants \(=\) Total mass of the products. Therefore, the law of multiple proportions is followed.
Amount of \(\mathrm{Fe}_{2} \mathrm{O}_{3}\) can be increased by taking any one of the reactants (iron or oxygen) in excess.
Amount of \(\mathrm{Fe}_{2} \mathrm{O}_{3}\) produced will decrease if the amount of any one of the reactants (iron or oxygen) is taken in excess.

1.q_string: Which of the following reactions is not correct according to the law of conservation of mass?
If the density of a solution is \(3.12 \mathrm{~g} / \mathrm{mL}\), the mass of \(1.5 \mathrm{~ml}\) solution in significant figures is:

\(2.00 \mathrm{~gm}\) of sample containing \(\mathrm{Na}_{2} \mathrm{CO}_{3}\) and \(\mathrm{NaHCO}_{3}\) loses \(0.248 \mathrm{~g}\) when heated to \(300^{\circ} \mathrm{C}\), the temperature at which \(\mathrm{NaHCO}_{3}\) decomposes. Find the percentage composition of \(\mathrm{Na}_{2} \mathrm{CO}_{3}\) in the mixture?

A sample of neon gas is contained by a closed 4-litre vessel. The temperature of container is \(25^{\circ} \mathrm{C}\) and pressure is \(1.5\) atmospheres.Neon gas in the vessel is replaced with an equal molar quantity of helium gas. Which of the following properties of the gas in the container will be changed? (The gas constant \((\mathrm R)=0.08 \mathrm{L~atm} / \mathrm{mol} / \mathrm{K}\) ).

Hemoglobin contains \(0.334 \%\) of iron by weight. The molecular weight of hemoglobin is approximately \(67200\). The number of iron atoms (Atomic weight of Fe is \(56\) ) present in one molecule of hemoglobin is:

Which one of the following is correct regarding Dalton's Atomic Theory?

  1. All atoms of a given element have identical properties, including identical mass. Atoms of different elements differ in mass.
  2. Compounds are formed when atoms of different elements combine in a fixed ratio.
  3. Chemical reactions involve re-organisation of atoms. These are neither created nor destroyed in a chemical reaction.
What will be the amount of water produced by the combustion of \(16 \mathrm{~g}\) of methane?

After the combustion the total volume of the gases was \(560 \mathrm{~mL}\) at STP. On treatment with \(\mathrm{KOH}\) the volume decreased to \(112 \mathrm{~mL}\). Which one of the molecular formula of the compound?

Line spectrum of element is unique and there is regularity in the line spectrum of each element. Which of the following line is observed in line spectrum of hydrogen atom?
One mole is the amount of a substance that contains as many particles or entities as there are atoms in ______________.
A given compound always contains exactly the same proportion of elements by weight. This law is stated by:

\(\mathrm{Cu}_{2} \mathrm{S}\) and \(\mathrm M_{2} \mathrm{S}\) are isomorphous in which percentage of sulphur is \(20.149\) and \(12.94 \%\) respectively. The atomic weight of \(\mathrm{M}\) is:

[Atomic wt. of \(\mathrm{Cu}=63.5]\)

Two gases \(\mathrm{A}\) and \(\mathrm{B}\) are taken in same volume containers under similar conditions of temperature and pressure. In container \(\mathrm{A}\), there are ' \(2 \mathrm{~N}\) ' molecules of gas \(\mathrm{A}\). The number molecules does container \(\mathrm{B}\) have:
Which one of the following is correct regarding empirical formula of a compound?
q_option: It represents the simplest whole number ratio of various atoms present in a compound.
It represents the simplest whole number ratio of the elements present in a compound
It represents the simplest ratio of masses of various elements  present in a compound
It represents the simplest average fractional ratio of various atoms present in a compound
